<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,1055,1981]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,1159,1184]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Differential Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Differentiated from all other species of American 
<taxonomicName box="[1035,1147,1160,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1035,1147,1160,1184]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Hydraena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except 
<taxonomicName box="[1241,1394,1160,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multispina">
<emphasis box="[1241,1394,1160,1184]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. multispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the spinose elytral apices and spinose labrum (
<figureCitation box="[682,822,1194,1218]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 21" captionStart-1="FIGURE 22" captionStartId-0="85.[151,250,1650,1673]" captionStartId-1="86.[151,250,1650,1673]" captionTargetBox-0="[253,1331,193,1626]" captionTargetBox-1="[305,1294,233,1606]" captionTargetId-0="figure@85.[253,1334,193,1629]" captionTargetId-1="figure@86.[270,1317,193,1629]" captionTargetPageId-0="85" captionTargetPageId-1="86" captionText-0="FIGURE 21. Hydraena multispina, holotype, dorsal and lateral habitus, and venter." captionText-1="FIGURE 22. Hydraena cordispina, holotype female, dorsal and lateral habitus, and venter." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/1050084/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/1050086/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Figs. 
<number box="[747,822,1194,1218]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="21.5" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="21.0">21–22</number>
</figureCitation>
). Refer to the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName box="[1131,1285,1195,1219]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multispina">
<emphasis box="[1131,1285,1195,1219]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. multispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for comparisons of the two species.
</paragraph>
